COVID-19 Status 💉 🦠

As of 2:49PM PT today, over 1.7 million Canadians have tested positive for COVID-19. Sadly, 29.1 thousand have died.

In the last day, 1.8 thousand new infections were reported and 32 deaths. Currently 1,977 are in the hospital and 591 are in the ICU. This is trending upwards.

Fortunately, 58.8 million doses of the vaccine have been administered. For those 12 years and older, 8.6% have their 1st shot and 15% are fully vaccinated!

Vaccination is slowing down, but there are 6 million doses in the freezer. It currently takes ~90 days for new deliveries to get into arms.

At the current rate, Canadians should achieve herd immunity around Nov-29 when 80% of the entire population is fully vaccinated. There is no approved vaccine for children aged 11 or younger.

  • 80 in 100 have at least one vaccine dose,
    68 in 100 are fully vaccinated. From storage
    20 in 100 more could receive a dose.
    Herd immunity is estimated at ~80%
